      "message": "It\u0027s not quite clear from this comment if the \"This\" refers to the Exception or the \"latch.getCount() \u003e 0\". It is hard to see how the latchCount can be greater than zero though? How can the parent cancel the connection without the other direction having already countDowned its latch in the finally below? Is it because a failure occurs in the parent (not in the other forwarder) before even entering the other \"forward\" method?",
